HEADWORD: Intrafusion
<hw>In`tra*fu"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>intra-</ets> + L. <ets>fundere</ets>, <ets>fusum</ets>, to
pour.]</ety> <def>The act of pouring into a vessel; specif.
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, the operation of introducing a substance into a blood
vessel; <as>as, <ex>intrafusion</ex> of blood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

